{"title_page": "Indian Institute of Management Ranchi", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{COI|date=June 2018}}\n{{advert|date=June 2018}}\n{{overly detailed|date=June 2018}}\n}}\n\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2014}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name           = Indian Institute of Management Ranchi\n|native_name    = \n|image_name     = Indian_Institute_of_Management_Ranchi.svg\n|motto          = Bahumukhvikaso gantavya\n|mottoeng       = Working to bring change towards success, not only for one\u2019s self, but also for the community.\n|established    = 2009\n|type           = [[Public university|Public]] [[Business School]]\n|director       = Shailendra Singh<ref>{{cite web|title=Director\u2019s Message|url=https://www.iimranchi.ac.in/?page_id=125|accessdate=14 July 2017|ref=Indian Institute of Management Ranchi}}</ref>\n|chairman       = Pravin Shankar Pandya<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pathak|first1=Vikas|title=Four IIMs to get new chairmen|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/four-iims-to-get-new-chairmen/article19695142.ece|accessdate=11 October 2017|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=16 September 2017|language=en-IN}}</ref>\n|campus         = Urban\n|city           = [[Ranchi]]\n|coor           = {{coord|23|23|0.19|N|85|18|57.31|E|region:IN|display=inline,title}}\n|state          = [[Jharkhand]]\n|country        = [[India]]\n|website        = {{URL|http://www.iimranchi.ac.in/}}\n}}\nThe '''Indian Institute of Management Ranchi''' ('''IIM Ranchi | IIM-R<ref>{{cite news|title= Successful-Summer-Placement|url=https://www.dailypioneer.com/2020/state-editions/iim-r-records-successful-summer-placement.html }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= IIM-R-gets-a-Home|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/india/iim-r-gets-a-home-minister-pallam-raju-sets-global-agenda/cid/279240#.UfbvV9L-Hmk }}</ref>''') is a public [[business school]] located in [[Ranchi]], [[Jharkhand]], [[India]]. IIM Ranchi was established at Ranchi on December 15, 2009 and began classes on July 6, 2010, under the 11th Five Year Plan.<ref name=\"MHRD notification\">{{cite news|title=MHRD notification|url=https://mhrd.gov.in/technical-education-3 }}</ref>\n\nInaugurated on 6 July 2010,<ref>{{cite news|title=IIM Ranchi opens doors on July 6|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1100629/jsp/jharkhand/story_12622897.jsp | location=Calcutta, India | work=The Telegraph|date=2010-06-29}}</ref> IIM Ranchi offers two-year Masters in Business Administration (MBA) and Masters in Business Administration - Human Resource Management (MBA-HRM), four<ref>https://www.iimranchi.ac.in/?page_id=1001</ref>-year Fellowship Programme and Executive Programmes.\n\n==History==\n{{unreferenced section|date=February 2018}}\nThe 11th [[Five-Year plans of India|Five-Year Plan]],<ref name=\"MHRD notification\"/> endorsed by the [[National Development Council (India)|National Development Council]] in December 2007, envisaged the establishment of six new IIMs.\n\nIIM Ranchi, like all IIMs, is an autonomous institution under the Ministry of Human Resources Development, Government of India. The institute is free to design its own curriculum and recruit faculty members. In April 2011, Union Minister Kapil Sibal announced that the government is mulling enhancement of the autonomy of IIMs by allowing them to select the director and the chairman of the Board of Directors.\n\nIIM Ranchi is amongst the six new IIMs that were approved by the Union Cabinet on 27 August 2009. [[M. J. Xavier]] was the founding director of the institute.\n[[File:IIM Ranchi Academic Building.jpg|thumb|IIM Ranchi Academic Building]]\n\n==Campus==\nThe college operates from a temporary campus in Suchana Bhavan, behind the Governor House premises in the heart of Ranchi. The student hostels of IIM Ranchi are located at Khelgaon.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1100317/jsp/frontpage/story_12225510.jsp |title=The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) &#124; Frontpage &#124; 15000 line up to join Ranchi IIM |publisher=Telegraphindia.com |date=2010-03-17 |accessdate=2012-02-25 |location=Calcutta, India |first=Amit |last=Gupta}}</ref>\n\nThe construction of a permanent campus has begun at Birhar village on the [[Khunti]]-[[Karra]] road, about {{convert|35|km}} from Ranchi.In July 2013,Jharkhand government allotted  {{convert|90.14|acre}} of land free of cost to IIM Ranchi (IIM-R) at Cheri in Kanke block, 20&nbsp;km from [[Ranchi]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-07-13/news/40553640_1_nagri-land-government-land-fertile-land | work=The Times Of India | title=IIM-Ranchi gets free land for campus - The Times of India}}</ref> On 29 July 2013, the Union Minister of Human Resource Development Shri [[Pallam Raju]] laid the foundation stone of IIM-Ranchi at Cheri.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1130730/jsp/frontpage/story_17172617.jsp#.UfbvV9L-Hmk | location=Calcutta, India | work=The Telegraph | first=A.S.R.P. | last=Mukesh | title=IIM-R gets a home | date=30 July 2013}}</ref>\n[[File:IIM Ranchi Hostel, Khelgaon.jpg|thumb|IIM Ranchi Hostel, Khelgaon]]\n\n==Academics==\nIIM Ranchi offers a master's degree in management as per the approval of the [[Indian Institute of Management Bill, 2017]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Cabinet Approves IIM Bill|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/education/cabinet-approves-iim-bill-2017/|accessdate=4 February 2017|publisher=Indian Express}}</ref> The two-year full-time residential programs: MBA and MBA-HRM are the two programmes under which students are awarded degrees. IIM Ranchi also offers doctoral-level fellowship programmes and a part-time executive program (PGEXP).<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.pagalguy.com/2011/07/iim-ranchi-to-start-part-time-pgpex-for-local-companies |title=IIM Ranchi to start part-time PGPEX for local companies |work=pagalguy.com |accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Rankings==\n{{Infobox India university ranking\n|type=Institute\n| NIRF_B_2019= 28\n}}\n\nIIM Ranchi was ranked 28 by the [[National Institutional Ranking Framework]] (NIRF) management ranking in 2019.<ref name=Rankings_NIRF_B_2019/>\n\n== Admissions ==\nAdmission to courses at IIM Ranchi is done based upon merit in [[Common Admission Test]], conducted by the IIMs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catiim.in/pdf/CAT_Advertisement.pdf|title=Indian Institute of Management (IIMs) - Common Admission Test (CAT) 2012|date=|format=PDF|accessdate=2012-08-10}}</ref>\n\n==Student Activities==\nIIM Ranchi is a completely student-driven business school. All the student bodies, such as Committees, Clubs, SIGs and Independent Bodies at IIM Ranchi, are managed by the students themselves and are governed by the Council for Student Affairs led by Senate members.\n\nThe Senate consists of four elected Senators from the Student Association of IIM Ranchi. They are responsible for spearheading student activities and acting as a liaison between the college administration and the students. The Council for Student Affairs also consists of seven Committee representatives, who along with Senate form the Student Council of IIM Ranchi.\n\nThere are a total of seven committees that form the backbone of IIM Ranchi's functioning namely:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iimranchi.ac.in/?page_id=9485|title=Student Committees {{!}} IIM Ranchi|website=www.iimranchi.ac.in|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n# '''Academic Committee''' \n# '''Alumni and International Relations Committee'''\n# '''Cultural Committee'''\n# '''Media & PR Cell'''\n# '''Sports Committee'''\n# '''Student Facilities Committee'''\n# '''Technology Committee'''\n\nThere are a total of 8 Clubs which drive IIM Ranchi:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iimranchi.ac.in/?page_id=9696|title=Student Clubs {{!}} IIM Ranchi|website=www.iimranchi.ac.in|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n# The Marketing Club ''''Marquess'''' \n# The Finance Club ''''Finopsis''''\n# The Operations and General Management Club ''''Sankriya''''\n# The Social Responsibility Club ''''Samarpan''''\n# The Consulting Club ''''Conundrum''''\n# The Entrepreneurship Club ''''E-Cell''''\n# The HR Club ''''HiRe'''' and\n# The ''''Literary Club''''\n\nIIM Ranchi has 9 Special Interest Groups (SIGs), which are associations of like-minded students working towards attaining proficiency in a special interest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iimranchi.ac.in/?page_id=9924|title=Self-Interest Groups {{!}} IIM Ranchi|website=www.iimranchi.ac.in|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n \n* High Note: Official Music band \n* Froggy Feet: Official Dance group \n* Dramebaaz: Dramatics Society \n* SOUL: Society for Objective and Unified Learning \n* Greyscale: Official creative group of IIMR \n* PRISM: IIMR\u2019s Placement Resources and Information Sharing Medium \n* Polynomics: The Economics and Public Policy Group \n* Digitalytics: The Analytics SIG \n* QR Code: The Quizzing fraternity of IIMR\n\nIIM R also has independent bodies that function autonomously in tandem with Student Council to fulfil the Institute's goals in various domains.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iimranchi.ac.in/?page_id=9950|title=Independent Bodies {{!}} IIM Ranchi|website=www.iimranchi.ac.in|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n# UNGC-PRME IIM Ranchi\n# IIM Ranchi Toastmasters\n# Visual Branding and Content Body (VBCB)\n# Institute's Innovation Council - IIM Ranchi\n# Counseling Cell\n# Gender Sensitization Committee\n# Placement Committee has a responsibility to foster corporate relations and conduct of the summer and final placement process.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iimranchi.ac.in/?page_id=189|title=Placement Committee  {{!}} IIM Ranchi|website=www.iimranchi.ac.in|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n== Conclaves and Conferences ==\n;AGON - The Annual Management Fest\nWith events in the various business fields of finance, marketing, consulting, human resources and communications, organized in the form of case studies, quizzes, essays, debates and more, AGON draws huge participation from local and national colleges.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.agon-iimranchi.com/|title=AGON IIM RANCHI|website=www.agon-iimranchi.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-03}}</ref>\n\n;AAROHAN Leadership Speak Series\nIIM Ranchi hosted its first leadership speak series named \"Aarohan\" on January 8, 2016 at Cockerel Stadium, Dipatoli cantonment, Ranchi. The idea of this is to invite role models across various fields to come and address the IIM Ranchi community, particularly the students. It is a leadership talk series aimed at student interaction with leaders and innovators of their respective fields to promote intellectual growth, stimulation and facilitate the development of a more inclusive world-view. Lt Gen Arun Kumar Sahni, Uttam Yudh Seva Medal, ADC, General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, South Western Command of Indian Army and Dr. Y.V.N. Krishna Murthy, Director, National Remote Sensing Centre, ISRO have been a part of the series<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iimranchi.ac.in/?page_id=6652|title=AAROHAN Leadership Speak Series  {{!}} IIM Ranchi|website=www.iimranchi.ac.in|language=en-US|access-date=2017-09-03}}</ref> \n; Colloquium\nColloquium is an annual series of guest lectures, where students of IIM Ranchi get an opportunity to interact with the industry leaders in finance, marketing, operations and HR that happen throughout the year. The speakers also deliver insights along with discussions on various contemporary issues faced by India.Some of the renowned speakers are: Mr. Amar Abrol, MD and CEO, AirAsia India. Mr. Amit Vaish, Director and Head HR, Barclays India. Mr. Satish Shah, Head of Human Capital, De Shaw India. Mr. Anirudh Patil, Director of Strategy & Operations, McKinsey & Co. Mr. Shashank Saxena, Vice President of Technology, Morgan Stanley.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailypioneer.com/state-editions/ranchi/colloquium-2014-15-kicks-off-at-iim-ranchi.html|title=Colloquium 2014-15 kicks off at IIM Ranchi|last=Pioneer|first=The|work=The Pioneer|access-date=2017-09-03|language=en}}</ref>\n;HR Conclave\nIIM Ranchi being the only IIM to offer specialised course in Human Resource Management, have organised two HR conclaves themed as \"Turning the tide on unrest in workforce \" in 2012 and \"Holistic Development of Human Capital\" in 2011, leaders across industry discussed the challenges faced by organizations and the role of HR managers in solving those challenges. Dignitaries like K.A. Narayan, President-HR, Raymond, Mr. Sandeep Choudhary, Partner, Aon Hewitt, Mr. Partha Dasgupta, CEO, Apogee Leads, Mr. R. Sridhar, Vice President-HR, ITC Limited any many others discussed about HR practices.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-22/ranchi/34021390_1_iim-ranchi-hr-conclave-maruti-chairman|title=HR conclave at IIM Ranchi - The Times of India|work=The Times Of India}}</ref>\n\n; RADIX- The Annual Business Conclave\nBased on the themes \"Connect,\" \"Enthuse,\" and \"Foster,\" Radix connects students with industry leaders. The aim is to facilitate a quality interaction among the experts and the students along with exchange of ideas regarding various industrial growth factors and the development of a shared vision for the future. Leaders from organizations such as KPMG, Ernst & Young, Lenovo, Godrej etc. have been a part of Radix 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.radix-iimranchi.com/|title=Radix IIM RANCHI|website=www.radix-iimranchi.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-03}}</ref>\n; RUSH- The Annual Sports and Cultural Fest\nThis two-day festival, the flagship of IIM Ranchi, includes events like Cricket, Lawn Tennis, Football, Athletics, Volleyball, Badminton (Men/Women), Table Tennis (Men/Women), Throwball, Theme Photography, Solo Dance, Duet Dance, War of Bands, T-shirt painting, Comedy Shayari etc.,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rush-iimranchi.com/|title=RUSH IIM RANCHI|website=www.rush-iimranchi.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-03}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of universities in India]]\n* [[Indian Institutes of Management]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.iimranchi.ac.in IIM Ranchi official website]\n\n{{Indian Institutes of Management}}\n{{South Chotanagpur Division topics}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Indian Institute Of Management Ranchi}}\n[[Category:Indian Institute of Management Ranchi| ]]\n[[Category:Indian Institutes of Management|Ranchi]]\n[[Category:Business schools in Jharkhand]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Ranchi]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2009]]\n[[Category:2009 establishments in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{COI|date=June 2018}}\n{{advert|date=June 2018}}\n{{overly detailed|date=June 2018}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2014}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name           = Indian Institute of Management Ranchi\n|native_name    = \n|image_name     = Indian_Institute_of_Management_Ranchi.svg\n|motto          = Bahumukhvikaso gantavya\n|mottoeng       = Working to bring change towards success, not only for one\u2019s self, but also for the community.\n|established    = 2009\n|type           = [[Public university|Public]] [[Business School]]\n|director       = Shailendra Singh<ref>{{cite web|title=Director\u2019s Message|url=https://www.iimranchi.ac.in/?page_id=125|accessdate=14 July 2017|ref=Indian Institute of Management Ranchi}}</ref>\n|chairman       = Pravin Shankar Pandya<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pathak|first1=Vikas|title=Four IIMs to get new chairmen|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/four-iims-to-get-new-chairmen/article19695142.ece|accessdate=11 October 2017|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=16 September 2017|language=en-IN}}</ref>\n|campus         = Urban\n|city           = [[Ranchi]]\n|coor           = {{coord|23|23|0.19|N|85|18|57.31|E|region:IN|display=inline,title}}\n|state          = [